          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                  <dt>Publication History</dt>
          <dd>
                                        <p>
                               Earl S. Johnston, "Lauds Exhibit of Two Artists Here", <em>The Patriot [Harrisburg]</em> (Harrisburg PA, December 9, 1936)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                               "Portraits by Polly Thayer at Philadelphia Art Alliance", <em>Philadelphia Inquirer</em> (November 8, 1936)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                               A. Z. Kruse, "At the Art Galleries", <em>Brooklyn (NY) Eagle</em> (November 16, 1941)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                               Rosamund Frost, "Polly Thayer", <em>Art News</em> (November 15, 1941 - November 30, 1941)
                                            </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Timothy Anglin Burgard, "Polly Thayer and May Sarton: Portrait of the Artists as Young Women", <em>Review / Harvard University Art Museums</em> (Cambridge, MA, Spring 1994), ill. p. 9
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Erica E. Hirshler, <em>A Studio of Her Own: Women Artists in Boston 1870-1940</em>, exh. cat., MFA Publications (Boston, MA, 2001), pl. 82
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Judith A. Curtis, <em>Polly Thayer Starr (1904-2006) & the Alchemy of Painting</em>, exh. cat., Rockport Art Association & Museum (Rockport, MA, 2017), p. 34, fig. 15, ill. (color)
                             </p>
                                    </dd>
        
                  <dt>Exhibition History</dt>
          <dd>
                          <p>
                              <em>Portraits by Polly Thayer</em>, Philadelphia Art Alliance, Philadelphia, 11/02/1936 - 11/15/1936
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>Polly Thayer</em>, Harrisburg Art Association, Harrisburg, 12/07/1936 - 12/13/1936
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>Polly Thayer (The 1941 Burton Emmett Memorial Exhibition)</em>, Contemporary Arts Gallery (NY), New York, 11/01/1941 - 12/01/1941
                            </p>
                          <p>
                              <em>The Persistence of Memory: Continuity and Change in American Cultures</em>, Harvard University Art Museums, Cambridge, 07/29/1995 - 05/13/2001
                            </p>
                      </dd>
        
        

        
      
      
        
